{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/blog/a-reason-why-photoshop-cs4-kicks-ass/","webpackCompilationHash":"3df84c5a931315f821fb","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"James Ford","author":"James Ford"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"0babeae9-7466-5d18-ab51-e65381beeefc","html":"<p>Here's one reason why Photoshop CS4 kicks ass (here's something completely new).</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 500px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/1af6fd42fab985ffed75ba9a2c14fc82/48a11/contentawarescale.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 55.99999999999999%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Content Aware Scale\"\n        title=\"Content Aware Scale\"\n        src=\"/static/1af6fd42fab985ffed75ba9a2c14fc82/48a11/contentawarescale.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/1af6fd42fab985ffed75ba9a2c14fc82/afcd2/contentawarescale.jpg 300w,\n/static/1af6fd42fab985ffed75ba9a2c14fc82/48a11/contentawarescale.jpg 500w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>It's called \"<strong>Content-Aware Scale</strong>\".  Unlike the transform controls from previous iterations, this scaling mode is somehow aware of the contents of an image and can discern what elements you want to scale.</p>\n<p>So when you start scaling up or down, only the elements like the sky, water, background elements stretch and the people and buildings maintain their perspective and float around the scaling background.  Pretty cool huh?</p>\n<p>So here's an image I've grabbed from Google - a panorama of <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trakai_Island_Castle\">Trakai Castle</a>.  In the image below I've scaled it to 50% width - the top image is \"Content-Aware Scale\", and the bottom image is shrunk with the normal transform tools.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 500px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/ac5957fc7301212f5c49599dfaaf7249/48a11/contentawareexample.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 62.6%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Content Aware Scale - Example\"\n        title=\"Content Aware Scale - Example\"\n        src=\"/static/ac5957fc7301212f5c49599dfaaf7249/48a11/contentawareexample.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/ac5957fc7301212f5c49599dfaaf7249/afcd2/contentawareexample.jpg 300w,\n/static/ac5957fc7301212f5c49599dfaaf7249/48a11/contentawareexample.jpg 500w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>That took 30 seconds to do.  How long would you previously spend cleverly masking and cloning areas of the image by hand to do that?</p>\n<p>How cool is that - it's image transformation, just like in the movies.  Next we'll be enhancing perfect images of suspects from pixellated CCTV footage, just like in CSI.</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"A reason why Photoshop CS4 kicks ass","date":"January 28, 2009","tags":null,"url":null,"image":null,"description":null,"image_credit":null}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"prev":{"frontmatter":{"path":"/blog/brighter-horizons-for-web-education/","tags":["external-links","education"],"title":"Brighter Horizons for Web Education","date":"2009-01-28T08:30:04.000Z","description":null,"image":null}},"next":{"frontmatter":{"path":"/blog/building-a-project-tracker-in-flex-air/","tags":["flex","air","subversion"],"title":"Building a project tracker in Flex & AIR","date":"2009-01-29T09:08:10.000Z","description":null,"image":{"childImageSharp":{"sizes":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","aspectRatio":1.7857142857142858,"src":"/static/4cb18a2fe60bc47054f6acc202910476/32ee9/bugsummary.jpg","srcSet":"/static/4cb18a2fe60bc47054f6acc202910476/10bdc/bugsummary.jpg 158w,\n/static/4cb18a2fe60bc47054f6acc202910476/f4ab0/bugsummary.jpg 315w,\n/static/4cb18a2fe60bc47054f6acc202910476/32ee9/bugsummary.jpg 500w","sizes":"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px"}}}}}}}}